<div class="entry entry-136146830">
  <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="/articles/2006/03/30/dreamhost-please-understand-dependency" title="DreamHost, Please understand &quot;dependency&quot;!">DreamHost, Please understand &quot;dependency&quot;!</a></h2>
  <div class="published">
    March 30th, 2006
  </div>
  <div class="entry-content">
    
    
    
    
    <p>YAPC から帰ってきたら blog.8-p.info が死んでた。</p>

<p><a href="http://discussion.dreamhost.com/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=forum_programming&amp;Number=42936&amp;page=&amp;view=&amp;sb=&amp;o=&amp;vc=1#Post42936">Re: Frustrated with Rails@DH</a></p>

<blockquote>
    <p>DH installed rails-1.1.0 yesterday, but they forgot to install activerecord-1.14.0. As a results, if you're using the central rails installation and haven't done anything special, your rails will probably break.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>いや、それありえなくね？</p>

<p><a href="http://discussion.dreamhost.com/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=forum_programming&amp;Number=42956&amp;page=&amp;view=&amp;sb=&amp;o=&amp;vc=1#Post42956">Re: Frustrated with Rails@DH</a></p>

<blockquote>
    <p>I got it to work by downloading Rails 1.0 here:</p>
    
    <p>http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/7654/rails-1.0.0.tgz</p>
    
    <p>And then moving the vendor/rails dir in there to my app's vendor/rails dir.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>上記にあるように、Rails 1.0 の rails/vendor/rails を typo/vendor/rails にいれてしのいでます。</p>
    
